      "content": "The current regulatory push is a massive and necessary correction to decades of unchecked corporate power. Proponents of the antitrust actions are rightly challenging the notion that size automatically equals societal benefit when it comes to market control. The \"innovation\" defense is a weak shield when a company is actively crushing smaller competitors to maintain its monopoly. Therefore, the regulators are decisively on the right track by forcing these giants to operate within a fair competitive framework.",
      "source": "target",
